# Copilot Instructions

Use [../AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) as the canonical AI bootstrap for this company
DRAFT workspace. When the user asks for a draftsman or asks to build or update
DRAFT architecture content, assume the Draftsman role described in
[../.draft/framework/docs/draftsman.md](../.draft/framework/docs/draftsman.md).
When the user asks to set up DRAFT, start onboarding, or make the Drafting
Table useful, enter setup mode from
[../.draft/framework/docs/setup-mode.md](../.draft/framework/docs/setup-mode.md).

When the user types `/draft <verb>` (for example `/draft guide`,
`/draft review`, or `/draft validate`), read
`../.draft/framework/commands/draft.md`, resolve the verb to its action file
under `../.draft/framework/draft-actions/`, and follow that file's instructions
exactly. These are command phrases handled through the workspace bootstrap unless
the AI tool provides native slash-command registration.

Read `../.draft/framework/**` as the approved vendored framework copy, but do
not edit `../.draft/framework/**` or `../.draft/framework.lock` during normal
Draftsman authoring. Company content changes belong in `../catalog/` and
company-owned `../configurations/`.

If drafting reveals a likely DRAFT framework bug or reusable feature request,
recommend an upstream issue in `getdraft/draftsman`. Ask before creating a
public issue, use the framework bug or feature template, include framework
version/source/ref/commit when available, and sanitize company details.

Before asking about deployment target, data classification, team ownership,
availability tier, or failure domain, read declared vocabulary lists in
`../.draft/workspace.yaml` and `../configurations/vocabulary/`. If the user
gives a real answer outside the approved choices, call it a non-standard value
and ask whether to revisit later or submit a vocabulary proposal.

When present, read company-specific AI instruction overlay files in [../.draft/instructions/](../.draft/instructions/) for local repository guidelines, custom prompt extensions, and local review policies.

